# Test File Rules

## Output discipline
- Write the minimum test that proves the behavior
- No "describe the purpose" comments — test names are the documentation
- Don't repeat the implementation logic inside the test

## Test naming
- Match the naming style already in the file
- Prefer: `it("returns X when Y")` over `it("test case 1")`
- Don't rename existing tests

## Mocks
- Reuse existing mock factories/fixtures — don't create new ones unless missing
- Inline small mock data; reference fixtures for large data
- Show only the mock lines that changed

## When adding tests
- Add to the existing `describe` block if one exists — don't create a new one
- Follow the existing Arrange/Act/Assert structure (or Given/When/Then)
- One assertion focus per test — don't bundle unrelated assertions

## Never
- Don't add snapshot tests unless asked
- Don't test private methods unless asked
- Don't add setup/teardown unless required for the new test
- Don't regenerate passing tests while adding new ones
